cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with Named Entity Recognition (NER), which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also makes use of structured data from DBpedia and Wikipedia, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases). The use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning and neural networks indicates that it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) in the sense that it is using public data sources to generate labeled datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR.
